title.rendered: Durban vs Joburg, South Africa T20 League 2022: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Durban: Quinton de Kock (c & wk), Matthew Breetzke, Heinrich Klaasen, Kyle Mayers*, Jason Holder*, Keemo Paul*, Wiaan Mulder, Dwaine Pretorius, Prenelan Subrayen, Keshav Maharaj, Akila Dananjaya*

Joburg: Kyle Verreynne (wk), Donavon Ferreira, Faf du Plessis (c), Janneman Malan, Leus du Plooy, Romario Shepherd, Nandre Burger, Aaron Phangiso, Lizaad Williams, Alzarri Joseph

Pitch Report

Venue: Kingsmead, Durban

(Based on the last 3 games)

1st innings average score: 133

2nd innings average score: 131

Wickets per innings: 6  

Type: Even contest between the bat and ball.

Weather: Slightly cloud but no rain forecast during the game.

Wins

Batting 1st: 67%

Batting 2nd: 33%

Fantasy Tips of the Day

At Kingsmead, Quinton de Kock has scored 257 runs at an average of 37 and a strike rate of 161 in 9 competitive T20s.

Reeza Hendricks, Matthew Breetzke, and Wiaan Mulder have appeared in the Ultimate Team in all their last 5 games.

In his last 2 games at the venue, Aaron Phangiso has conceded only 45 runs for a wicket.

Durban boast quality spinners in Keshav Maharaj and Akila Dananjaya. At the venue, Maharaj has managed as many as 42 wickets. Meanwhile, Dananjaya has a reputation for taking big wickets and bowling economical spells.
